    <div class="section" id="sec3">

    <div id="value1" class="step sec3" data-x="3540" data-y="-300" data-scale=".3">
		<h2>An Unboundednes Question</h2>

		<br/>

		<h3>Given a probabilistic automaton, do there exist words accepted with probability arbitrarily close to $1$?</h3>

		<br/>
		<div class="slide_step">
		<b>Sad story:</b> <i>Gimbert and Oualhadj (2010)</i>

		<br/>
		It is <b>undecidable</b>!
		</div>

		<div class="slide_step">
		<h3>But to <i>what extent</i>?</h3>
		</div>
    </div>

    <div id="value1_ex" class="step sec3" data-x="3660" data-y="-240" data-scale=".1">
	<img id="example_value1" src="img/pa.svg"></img>

	<br/>
	<br/>

	<ul>
		<li>No sequence of actions ensure to reach home almost surely</li>
		<li>For every $\varepsilon > 0$, there exists a sequence of actions ensuring to reach home with probability at least $1 - \varepsilon$</li>
		<li>This is not true anymore if the probabilities change!</li>
	</ul>
    </div>

    <!-- end of section 3 -->
    </div>

